==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nidulant
<hw>Nid"u*lant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nidulans</ets>, p. pr.: cf. F. <er>Nidulant</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Nestling, as a bird in its nest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Lying loose in pulp or cotton
within a berry or pericarp, as in a nest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nidulate</ent>⟦br⟧
